Once I own the context layer, new capabilities open up. Different tasks can be routed to different models based on sensitivity, cost, and complexity. Not one model for everything. The right model for each job.

Enterprise context needs classification, audit trails, and retention policies. Self-hosting gives granular control. Vendor memory offers none of it.

The widening gap: the longer I invest in a portable, governed context layer, the wider the gap between my AI capability and someone starting from scratch with a new model's blank memory.
